the palette of color from from karakoram highway onwards.  the simplification of color distills the form of the mountains so beautifully here - and the tone is instilled in the sky by  the wind whipping the brown dust into air.  it settles into every nook and cranny of your gear, and stains the silty drinking water collected from the glacial melt.  the shigar charges by, rolling boulders along it\'s brown roiling depths, filling the air with noises that sound like a low coffee grinder.\r\n\r\nstill low down here, in a junction of glacial valleys, but the drama is in the air - the big mountains are close.\r\n\r\nmerge of 7 photographs – Canon EF-S 15 -85 mm @ 18mm/f9.  Canon EOS Rebel T1i 1/60th second exposure @ ISO 200.  Camera Raw processed &amp; profiled with Adobe Photoshop CS5/Canon IPF 16 bit print plug-in for Photoshop.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_164\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"587\"]<img class=\" wp-image-164   \" alt=\"Detail View\" src=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/sunset_from_korophon_sample.jpg\" width=\"587\" height=\"396\" /> detail[/caption]','sunset from korophon','','publish','open','closed','','sunset-from-korophon','','','2013-12-07 21:06:48','2013-12-07 21:06:48','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=162',19,'product','',0),(163,1,'2013-11-12 04:31:53','2013-11-12 04:31:53','','sunset_from_korophon','','inherit','open','open','','sunset_from_korophon','','','2013-11-12 04:31:53','2013-11-12 04:31:53','',162,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/sunset_from_korophon.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(164,1,'2013-11-12 04:32:09','2013-11-12 04:32:09','','sunset_from_korophon_sample','Detail View','inherit','open','open','','sunset_from_korophon_sample','','','2013-11-12 04:32:09','2013-11-12 04:32:09','',162,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/sunset_from_korophon_sample.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(165,1,'2013-11-12 04:35:48','2013-11-12 04:35:48','<strong>Arun River Valley, Nepal</strong>\r\n\r\none of my primary goals for the last trek was to find more of the color green to put into the mountainscapes.  spring &amp; an early monsoon gave this opportunity from the village of tashigaun - on the way to makalu basecamp.\r\n\r\nthe green of this village oasis took on an added significance the farther we left it behind - for it is the last place where the benefits of fresh food &amp; a balanced diet are easily procured from here on up.  it was wonderful to return here after a couple of weeks up high and eat baby ferns from the jungle procured by our remarkable sherpa hosts.\r\n\r\nmerge of 8 photographs - Canon EF 24 -105 mm @ 28mm/f18.  Canon EOS 6D 1/80th second exposure @ ISO 400.  Camera Raw processed &amp; profiled with Adobe DNG Converter/Photoshop CS5/Canon IPF 16 bit print plug-in for Photoshop.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_403\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"585\"]<a href=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/sunrise_from_tashigaun_sample1.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-403 \" alt=\"sunrise_from_tashigaun_sample\" src=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/sunrise_from_tashigaun_sample1.jpg\" width=\"585\" height=\"396\" /></a> detail[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','sunrise from tashigaun','','publish','open','closed','','sunrise-from-tashigaun','','','2013-12-03 20:50:06','2013-12-03 20:50:06','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=165',3,'product','',0),(166,1,'2013-11-12 04:35:02','2013-11-12 04:35:02','','sunrise_from_tashigaun','','inherit','open','open','','sunrise_from_tashigaun','','','2013-11-12 04:35:02','2013-11-12 04:35:02','',165,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/sunrise_from_tashigaun.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(167,1,'2013-11-12 04:35:19','2013-11-12 04:35:19','','sunrise_from_tashigaun_sample','Detail View','inherit','open','open','','sunrise_from_tashigaun_sample','','','2013-11-12 04:35:19','2013-11-12 04:35:19','