d=\"attachment_287\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"212\"]<a href=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/barun_rhododendrons_SAMPLE.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-287 \" alt=\"barun_rhododendrons_SAMPLE\" src=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/barun_rhododendrons_SAMPLE.jpg\" width=\"212\" height=\"143\" /></a> sample[/caption]','rhododendron field on kauma la','','publish','open','closed','','rhododendron-field-on-kauma-la','','','2013-11-24 14:56:20','2013-11-24 14:56:20','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=285',42,'product','',0),(286,2,'2013-11-24 14:53:44','2013-11-24 14:53:44','','barun_rhododendrons','','inherit','open','open','','barun_rhododendrons','','','2013-11-24 14:53:44','2013-11-24 14:53:44','',285,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/barun_rhododendrons.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(287,2,'2013-11-24 14:55:30','2013-11-24 14:55:30','','barun_rhododendrons_SAMPLE','','inherit','open','open','','barun_rhododendrons_sample','','','2013-11-24 14:55:30','2013-11-24 14:55:30','',285,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/barun_rhododendrons_SAMPLE.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(288,2,'2013-11-24 14:58:55','2013-11-24 14:58:55','<strong>Nepal Himalaya</strong>\r\n\r\ndelightful day hike with purna and ramesh up the hill above the village of samdo to attain perspective on the manaslu himalaya lying across the upper valley.  this day found ramesh bahadur in fine form running up and down the mountain, and the coinage of the term huin ko bag - \"snow tiger\" - the kid is gifted in the mountains.\r\n\r\nnorth of the range here, and quite close to the border of tibet.  the budhi gandaki descends to the left, which we have followed up, and will now be departing from to ascend the larkya la, in the right center, a 5000 meter pass that is the high point of our circle around manaslu.  tucked away out of sight beneath the hill we are standing on is samdo, the last of the tibetan villages on the north side before the crossing.\r\n\r\nat least 3 different passes over the border nearby and yaks being herded up and sent over by traders and other men with teams of horses endlessly coming and going in their caravans.  it is also a crossroads for trekkers, for you must get over the larkya la in order to avoid a long trip back down the budhi gandaki.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_278\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"586\"]<a href=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/from_samdo_ri_sample.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-278  \" alt=\"from_samdo_ri_sample\" src=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/from_samdo_ri_sample.jpg\" width=\"586\" height=\"396\" /></a> detail[/caption]','manaslu himalaya from samdo ri','','publish','open','closed','','manaslu-himalaya-from-samdo-ri-2','','','2013-12-15 17:57:16','2013-12-15 17:57:16','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=288',31,'product','',0),(289,2,'2013-11-24 15:30:29','2013-11-24 15:30:29','<strong>karakoram range, pakistan</strong>','cathedral group & lobsang spires','','publish','open','closed','','cathedral-group-lobsang-spires','','','2013-11-24 15:30:29','2013-11-24 15:30:29','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=289',41,'product','',0),(290,2,'2013-11-24 15:29:23','2013-11-24 15:29:23','','cathedral_group_and_lobsang_spires','','inherit','open','open','','cathedral_group_and_lobsang_spires','','','2013-11-24 15:29:23','2013-11-24 15:29:23','',289,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/cathedral_group_and_lobsang_spires.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(291,2,'2013-11-24 15:32:46','2013-11-24 15:32:46','<strong>From Liligo Camp - Baltoro Glacier, Pakistan</strong>\r\n\r\nlast light on the lower baltoro &amp; not a cloud in the sky in liligo.  my trek mate ian had an 18 - 200 mm along so i borrowed it and went out to shoot cathedral spire.\r\n\r\nsingular in the power of its geometry, the cleanest shape in the whole valley, perfectly positioned to glow in the last light of day - cathedral spire is a shape that has inhabited the dreams of many a climber - an unadulterated idea of mountain form.\r\n\r\ncanon efs 18-200 @ 135mm f16 eos rebel t1i 1/400sec 200iso raw photoshop cs5 mac','cathedral spire (5866m)','','publish','open','closed','','cathedral-spire5866m','','','2013-12-05 18:31:44','2013-12-05 18:31:44','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=291',35,'product','',0),(292,2,'2013-11-24 15:31:28','2013-11-24 15:31:28','','cathedral_spire','','inherit','open','open','','cathedral_spire','','','2013-11-24 15:31:28','2013-11-24 15:31:28','',291,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/cathedral_spire.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(293,2,'2013-11-24 15:38:44','2013-11-24 15:38:44','<strong>from the trek around manaslu - nepal</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_295\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"211\"]<a href=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/dawn_from_bhimtang_sample.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-295  \" alt=\"sample\" src=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/dawn_from_bhimtang_sample.jpg\" width=\"211\" height=\"143\" /></a> detail[/caption]','dawn from bhimtang','','publish','open','closed','','dawn-from-bhimtang','','','2013-11-24 15:38:44','2013-11-24 15:38:44','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=293',39,'product','',0),(294,2,'2013-11-24 15:35:52','2013-11-24 15:35:52','','dawn_from_bhimtang','','inherit','open','open','','dawn_from_bhimtang','','','2013-11-24 15:35:52','2013-11-24 15:35:52','',293,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/dawn_from_bhimtang.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(295,2,'2013-11-24 15:37:11','2013-11-24 15:37:11','','dawn_from_bhimtang_sample','sample','inherit','open','open','','dawn_from_bhimtang_sample','','','2013-11-24 15:37:11','2013-11-24 15:37:11','',293,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/dawn_from_bhimtang_sample.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(296,2,'2013-11-24 15:57:44','2013-11-24 15:57:44','<strong>makalu मकालु (8481m)</strong>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_298\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"345\"]<a href=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/from_the_approach_to_sherpani_col_phedi_SAMPLE.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-298\" alt=\"from_the_approach_to_sherpani_col_phedi_SAMPLE\" src=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/from_the_approach_to_sherpani_col_phedi_SAMPLE.jpg\" width=\"345\" height=\"238\" /></a> detail[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','from the approach to sherpani col phedi','','publish','open','closed','','from-the-approach-to-sherpani-col-phedi','','','2013-11-24 15:57:44','2013-11-24 15:57:44','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=296',40,'product','',0),(297,2,'2013-11-24 15:40:03','2013-11-24 15:40:03','','from_the_approach_to_sherpani_col_phedi','','inherit','open','open','','from_the_approach_to_sherpani_col_phedi','','','2013-11-24 15:40:03','2013-11-24 15:40:03','',296,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/from_the_approach_to_sherpani_col_phedi.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(298,2,'2013-11-24 15:57:04','2013-11-24 15:57:04','','from_the_approach_to_sherpani_col_phedi_SAMPLE','','inherit','open','open','','from_the_approach_to_sherpani_col_phedi_sample','','','2013-11-24 15:57:04','2013-11-24 15:57:04','',296,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/from_the_approach_to_sherpani_col_phedi_SAMPLE.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(299,2,'2013-11-24 16:00:14','2013-11-24 16:00:14','<strong>From Concordia</strong>\r\n\r\ni had overlooked the twins.  one often does, surrounded as they are next to their larger brothers of the gasherbrum massif &amp; down the way from k2, but in exclusion they are revealed to be quite something in and of themselves.  esepcially with late day sun filtering through broken clouds above concordia, the junction of the baltoro and godwin-austen glaciers.  in concordia you are close to 4 of the 14 tallest mountains on earth, and only here, in this ultimate mountain panorama, could you possibly overlook something like the twins.','gasherbrum east twin (6882m)','','publish','open','closed','','gasherbrum-east-twin-6882m','','','2013-12-16 21:27:31','2013-12-16 21:27:31','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=299',36,'product','',0),(300,2,'2013-11-24 15:59:04','2013-11-24 15:59:04','','gasherbrum_east_twin','','inherit','open','open','','gasherbrum_east_twin','','','2013-11-24 15:59:04','2013-11-24 15:59:04','',299,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/gasherbrum_east_twin.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(301,2,'2013-11-24 16:03:41','2013-11-24 16:03:41','<strong>Annapurna Himalaya, Nepal</strong>\r\n\r\nthe recently opened mardi himal basecamp trek ascends a long ridge through rhododendron jungle and then above onto the flanks of the annapurna himalaya, under the shadow of the incomparable machhapuchare, or \"fishtail\".\r\n\r\nthis vista is called \"1st viewpoint\" and is the initial point at which you pop out of the trees enough to really see where you are.  it also showcases a very rare stand of pristine himalayan rhododendron, which i had taken as my primary photographic objective for the trek.  after passing here 2 times in tantalizingly close but not quite suitable photographic conditions my stubbornness would not let me leave without getting this shot.  i resolved to retrace my steps here after a nights rest below at the machhapuchare guesthouse, operated by the brothers bhim &amp; khim tamang.\r\n\r\ni really shared some fine times with those brothers - so alike looking but so different from one another - bhim scrupulous and polite to a fault, his english carefully crafted from 6 years of clerical work in saudi arabia.  he taught myself and my friends some superb card games, which became a staple of the trek from then on.  khim, the elder brother, shifty, opportunistic, but able to go with the plan - like when he told me where the local ganja grew or when i told him i would be getting up @ 3 am to go back up and get the shot.  and the 3rd time was a charm.\r\n\r\nmerge of 28 photographs – Canon EF 24 -105 mm @ 32mm/f22.  Canon EOS 6D 1/50th second exposure @ ISO 320.  Camera Raw processed &amp; profiled with Adobe DNG Converter/Photoshop CS5/Canon IPF 16 bit print plug-in for Photoshop.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_303\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"584\"]<a href=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/from_the_mardi_himalSAMPLE.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-303 \" alt=\"from_the_mardi_himalSAMPLE\" src=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/from_the_mardi_himalSAMPLE.jpg\" width=\"584\" height=\"396\" /></a> detail[/caption]','from the mardi himal','','publish','open','closed','','from-the-mardi-himal','','','2013-12-07 20:35:59','2013-12-07 20:35:59','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=301',7,'product','',0),(302,2,'2013-11-24 16:01:56','2013-11-24 16:01:56','','from_the_mardi_himalSRGB','','inherit','open','open','','from_the_mardi_himalsrgb','','','2013-11-24 16:01:56','2013-11-24 16:01:56','',301,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/from_the_mardi_himalSRGB.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(303,2,'2013-11-24 16:03:15','2013-11-24 16:03:15','','from_the_mardi_himalSAMPLE','','inherit','open','open','','from_the_mardi_himalsample','','','2013-11-24 16:03:15','2013-11-24 16:03:15','',301,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/from_the_mardi_himalSAMPLE.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(304,2,'2013-11-24 16:33:16','2013-11-24 16:33:16','<strong>From Concordia</strong>\r\n\r\na tip of the hat to roland, our tour leader, for snapping me out of high altitude lethargy to grab this one - his early morning observation of \"nice light on k2 now doug\" momentarily pulled my fragmented mind back together and i grabbed a couple outside the tent before groveling back in for more liquid and sit down time. 8 hrs later i was squirting said liquid out of both ends as i crawled back down the godwin-austen, but the impetus to rise and seize a once in a lifetime morning i attribute to my teammates. glad to be along for the ride that day.\r\n\r\nstitch of 4 photographs - canon efs 15-85 @ 85mm f5.6 eos rebel t1i 1/40sec 400iso raw photoshop cs5 mac\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_306\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"582\"]<a href=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/dawn_on_k2_sample.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-306  \" alt=\"detail\" src=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/dawn_on_k2_sample.jpg\" width=\"582\" height=\"396\" /></a> detail[/caption]','dawn on K2 (8611m)','','publish','open','closed','','dawn-on-k2-8611m','','','2013-12-18 20:49:23','2013-12-18 20:49:23','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=304',37,'product','',0),(305,2,'2013-11-24 16:31:56','2013-11-24 16:31:56','','dawn_on_k2','','inherit','open','open','','dawn_on_k2','','','2013-11-24 16:31:56','2013-11-24 16:31:56','',304,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/dawn_on_k2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(306,2,'2013-11-24 16:32:48','2013-11-24 16:32:48','','dawn_on_k2_sample','detail','inherit','open','open','','dawn_on_k2_sample','','','2013-11-24 16:32:48','2013-11-24 16:32:48','',304,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/dawn_on_k2_sample.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(307,2,'2013-11-24 16:35:17','2013-11-24 16:35:17','<strong>From Muldea Viewpoint - Annapurna Himalaya, Nepal</strong>\r\n\r\nmuldea view lies within new trekking territory developing in the southwestern foothills of the annapurna himalaya.  the area is already world renowned for nearby poon hill and annapurna basecamp, and muldea only enhances the cornucopia of awesomeness this region has to offer for variety of amazing places to see.  from the viewpoint new vantages of annapurna south, fishtail, and dhaulagiri are visible.\r\n\r\na lovely gurung couple and their amazing son run a guesthouse in the outpost of dobato, lying below, which serves as the base for the climb of muldea, and lies as well within the tradition of impeccable gurung hospitality characteristic of the annapurna region.  radhav was also kind enough to show me a shortcut across the range to the east for my proposed crossing through rhododendron country in that direction.','Dhaulagiri I (8167 m)','','publish','open','closed','','dhaulagiri-i-8167-m','','','2013-12-14 19:09:45','2013-12-14 19:09:45','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=307',25,'product','',0),(308,2,'2013-11-24 16:33:59','2013-11-24 16:33:59','','dhaulagiri_from_muldea','','inherit','open','open','','dhaulagiri_from_muldea','','','2013-11-24 16:33:59','2013-11-24 16:33:59','',307,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/dhaulagiri_from_muldea.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(309,2,'2013-11-24 16:36:50','2013-11-24 16:36:50','<strong>Baltoro Glacier - Karakoram Range, Pakistan</strong>\r\n\r\nthe glacier has been designated a restricted area, lying close to the indian border and thus of perceived strategic significance to the pakistani army.  they post camps along the way to keep an eye on things &amp; individual trekking is not permitted.  meeting some of the men is reassuringly interesting, however, and the appearance of 80+ porters, a cook crew of 15, 3 pakistani guides, one western leader, 10 tourists, 3 goats, and a handful of chickens is bound to lead to some friendly commingling - not just with 3 lonely guys on outpost duty but with other tourist groups here from around the world to see the show.\r\n\r\ni find that expedition trekking, more expensive &amp; restrictive as opposed to the more freewheeling individual trekking, is not without certain logistical advantages.  the human to human time for tourists &amp; crew can provide a nice respite from the solitude of walking the mountains.  another advantage is  that having every logistical detail pre-arranged and dealt with in advance leaves lots of time to wander off &amp; shoot without having to worry about said details - it\'s hard to put a price tag on that.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','gore camp','','publish','open','closed','','gore-camp','','','2013-12-14 18:40:55','2013-12-14 18:40:55','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=309',23,'product','',0),(310,2,'2013-11-24 16:36:05','2013-11-24 16:36:05','','from_gore_camp','','inherit','open','open','','from_gore_camp','','','2013-11-24 16:36:05','2013-11-24 16:36:05','',309,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/from_gore_camp.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(312,2,'2013-11-24 17:43:08','2013-11-24 17:43:08','<strong>8th tallest mountain in the world</strong>','manaslu (8163m)','','publish','open','closed','','manaslu-8163m','','','2013-11-24 17:43:08','2013-11-24 17:43:08','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=312',38,'product','',0),(313,2,'2013-11-24 17:42:11','2013-11-24 17:42:11','','manaslu_8163m','','inherit','open','open','','manaslu_8163m','','','2013-11-24 17:42:11','2013-11-24 17:42:11','',312,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/manaslu_8163m.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(314,2,'2013-11-24 17:47:44','2013-11-24 17:47:44','<strong>From the climb of Tsergo Ri - Langtang Himalaya, Nepal</strong>\r\n\r\nprolonged exposure to trekking had taken my body to the point where my stomach was now a bottomless well which no amount of rice &amp; lentisl could be up to the task to fill.  i was summarily asked to leave one guesthouse after dinner one night by the local sisters who witnessed the carnage at the dinner table - they had 50 koreans &amp; accompanying support coming in on a 3 day so i was clearly expendable to their immediate plans.\r\n\r\nfeeling unwanted, i wandered out of the village at 2 a.m in order to attempt a night ascent of tsergo ri - a mound of rock from whose top one gets perspective on the west face of langtang lirung &amp; langtang II catching the first rays of sun from the east.  so peaceful to be trekking in the night, with the infinite stillness of these mountains as your intimate companion.  and the arrival of the day is the revelation of color.\r\n\r\nmerge of 2 photographs - Canon EF-S 15 -85 mm @ 31mm/f11.  Canon EOS Rebel T1i 1/80th second exposure @ ISO 200.  Camera Raw processed &amp; profiled with Adobe Photoshop CS5/Canon IPF 16 bit print plug-in for Photoshop.\r\n<div></div>','dawn on langtang lirung (7227m)','','publish','open','closed','','dawn-on-langtang-lirung-7227m','','','2013-12-02 02:14:58','2013-12-02 02:14:58','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=314',5,'product','',0),(315,2,'2013-11-24 17:46:02','2013-11-24 17:46:02','','dawn_on_langtang_lirung','','inherit','open','open','','dawn_on_langtang_lirung','','','2013-11-24 17:46:02','2013-11-24 17:46:02','',314,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/dawn_on_langtang_lirung.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(316,2,'2013-11-24 17:51:21','2013-11-24 17:51:21','<strong>From the Baltoro Glacier - Karakoram Range, Pakistan</strong>\r\n\r\ntook this one with young kai - a strapping english lad whose youthful energy i was drawn to and whose company suited me great while we shared a tent on the k2 trek.  we were wandering around gore camp after dinner during the perfect lengthening of a summer day in valhalla.\r\n\r\nto think of the paths we take and all of mine that had led me here to this dream - 10 years to get here it seemed &amp; this brilliant kid was coming here in his early 20\'s.\r\n\r\ni remember my early 20\'s and how it was the beginning of your professional path - if i had come here then as opposed to 20 years later would my path have turned differently?\r\n\r\nmerge of 5 photographs - Canon EF-S 15 -85 mm @ 35mm/f25.  Canon EOS Rebel T1i 1/60th second exposure @ ISO 200.  Camera Raw processed &amp; profiled with Adobe Photoshop CS5/Canon IPF 16 bit print plug-in for Photoshop.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','masherbrum & penitentes II','','publish','open','closed','','masherbrum-penitentes-ii','','','2013-12-02 01:56:31','2013-12-02 01:56:31','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=316',4,'product','',0),(317,2,'2013-11-24 17:50:22','2013-11-24 17:50:22','','masherbrum_and_penitentes_2','','inherit','open','open','','masherbrum_and_penitentes_2','','','2013-11-24 17:50:22','2013-11-24 17:50:22','',316,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/masherbrum_and_penitentes_2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(318,2,'2013-11-24 18:41:40','2013-11-24 18:41:40','<strong>Karakoram Range, Pakistan</strong>\r\n\r\na 2 minute opening of opportunity in 3 days of storm, a small window opened in the clouds  - sun and window aligning paths momentarily in their trajectories, to create beam of light on the trango group across the valley from where i stood on the hillside above urdukas.\r\n\r\nthe sunlight reveals the south and east wall of great trango (6286m), a wall in the running for the title of most precipitous cliff in the world.  next to it, also bathed in morning light, is nameless tower.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','great trango & nameless tower','','publish','open','closed','','great-trango-nameless-tower','','','2013-12-15 17:20:25','2013-12-15 17:20:25','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=318',30,'product','',0),(319,2,'2013-11-24 18:40:48','2013-11-24 18:40:48','','great_trango_and_nameless_tower','','inherit','open','open','','great_trango_and_nameless_tower','','','2013-11-24 18:40:48','2013-11-24 18:40:48','',318,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/great_trango_and_nameless_tower.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(320,2,'2013-11-24 18:43:13','2013-11-24 18:43:13','<strong>From Gore Camp</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>one of my primary objectives for this trek was to document alpenglow on \"the shining wall\" - the west face of gasherbrum IV (7912m).  i was lucky with weather this night and really could just spend an evening together with this geometrically perfect icon of the baltoro mustagh - the subrange of the karakoram where the mountains attain similar scale to the high himalaya yet their architecture is bolder, with sharper angles cleaved from a sterner cloth.  they stand to me symbolically as the profoundest mountain range on earth.\r\n\r\nlens info','dusk on the gasherbrum massif','','publish','open','closed','','dusk-on-the-gasherbrum-massis','','','2013-12-15 15:56:27','2013-12-15 15:56:27','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=320',28,'product','',0),(321,2,'2013-11-24 18:42:23','2013-11-24 18:42:23','','dusk_on_the_gasherbrum_massif','','inherit','open','open','','dusk_on_the_gasherbrum_massif','','','2013-11-24 18:42:23','2013-11-24 18:42:23','',320,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/dusk_on_the_gasherbrum_massif.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(324,2,'2013-11-24 19:00:41','2013-11-24 19:00:41','<strong>Karakoram Range, Pakistan</strong>\r\n\r\none of the crueler fates assigned to a creature would be the toil of a pack horse on the baltoro - the terrain is nothing if not leg breaking &amp; many of their sad &amp; desiccated carcasses litter the glacier and put the blot of man on gods immaculate work.  a barbaric practice that unfortunately still economically justifies itself as horses do not go on strike or change the deal and a horse can carry more without complaint and yet his life is worth less.\r\n\r\nthis i feel compelled to mention even as i have exploited these animals myself to provide perspective for the awesome dimensions of the karakoram.  i pray for their salvation and hope that perhaps the decline of tourism in pakistan, so tragic to me on a deeply personal level, will reduce the use of pack horses to carry supplies on the baltoro.\r\n\r\nmerge of 23 photographs – Canon EF-S 15 -85 mm @ 19mm/f20.  Canon EOS Rebel T1i 1/125th second exposure @ ISO 200.  Camera Raw processed &amp; profiled with Adobe Photoshop CS5/Canon IPF 16 bit print plug-in for Photoshop.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_326\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"574\"]<a href=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/horses_on_the_baltoro_SAMPLE.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-326  \" alt=\"detail\" src=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/horses_on_the_baltoro_SAMPLE.jpg\" width=\"574\" height=\"396\" /></a> detail[/caption]','horses on the baltoro','','publish','open','closed','','horses-on-the-baltoro','','','2013-12-07 22:13:25','2013-12-07 22:13:25','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=324',22,'product','',0),(325,2,'2013-11-24 18:59:16','2013-11-24 18:59:16','','horses_on_the_baltoro','','inherit','open','open','','horses_on_the_baltoro','','','2013-11-24 18:59:16','2013-11-24 18:59:16','',324,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/horses_on_the_baltoro.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(326,2,'2013-11-24 19:00:08','2013-11-24 19:00:08','','horses_on_the_baltoro_SAMPLE','detail','inherit','open','open','','horses_on_the_baltoro_sample','','','2013-11-24 19:00:08','2013-11-24 19:00:08','',324,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/horses_on_the_baltoro_SAMPLE.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(327,2,'2013-11-24 19:03:19','2013-11-24 19:03:19','<strong>From the Trek Around Manaslu, Nepal</strong>\r\n\r\none of our earliest adventures off the beaten track, with my local guys purna &amp; ramesh, to this vista from above the village of sama.  we were able to bushwhack up the hill behind the village to a ridge that crested treeline and gave views across to the kutang himalaya basking in the setting sun.  ramesh was 18 years old then &amp; in his element, oftentimes using branches &amp; vines to support hurtling himself through the steep terrain.\r\n\r\nin my eagerness i had pressed to accomplish this foray up the hill soon after our arrival in sama, but i had not yet learned the lesson that for me trekking north of the himalaya in winter is more difficult than trekking south of the range - we frequently had a giant mountain between us and the sun, and the solar warmth of the southern aspects makes all the difference for me. being cold &amp; in the shade had added quite a few meters as to how i was feeling in regards the altitude, but you can\'t let that stand in your way sometimes - who knows when you will ever come back?\r\n\r\nso i remember suffering a little for this one &amp; afterwards retreating back down to a lower village in order to clear a raging migraine.  but from this point i could clearly make out a saddle that promised a possible future attempt on sama ri, which was a major coup for us i thought.  and we were able to go to a new vantage point to take some mountainscapes, and not for the last time.  cheers to that.\r\n\r\nmerge of 8 photographs – Canon EF-S 15 -85 mm @ 15mm/f8.  Canon EOS Rebel T1i 1/320th second exposure @ ISO 400.  Camera Raw processed &amp; profiled with Adobe Photoshop CS5/Canon IPF 16 bit print plug-in for Photoshop.\r\n<div></div>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_329\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"586\"]<a href=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/kutang_himalaya_from_above_sama_SAMPLE.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-329  \" alt=\"detail\" src=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/kutang_himalaya_from_above_sama_SAMPLE.jpg\" width=\"586\" height=\"396\" /></a> detail[/caption]','kutang himalaya from above sama','','publish','open','closed','','kutang-himalaya-from-above-sama','','','2013-12-14 17:42:15','2013-12-14 17:42:15','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=327',21,'product','',0),(328,2,'2013-11-24 19:01:48','2013-11-24 19:01:48','','kutang_himalaya_from_above_sama','','inherit','open','open','','kutang_himalaya_from_above_sama','','','2013-11-24 19:01:48','2013-11-24 19:01:48','',327,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/kutang_himalaya_from_above_sama.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(329,2,'2013-11-24 19:02:48','2013-11-24 19:02:48','','kutang_himalaya_from_above_sama_SAMPLE','detail','inherit','open','open','','kutang_himalaya_from_above_sama_sample','','','2013-11-24 19:02:48','2013-11-24 19:02:48','',327,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/kutang_himalaya_from_above_sama_SAMPLE.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(330,2,'2013-11-24 19:19:01','2013-11-24 19:19:01','<strong>Sunrise from Ranipauwa - Rasuwa District, Nepal</strong>\r\n<p id=\"yui_3_11_0_3_1386450473510_1558\">a \"chakkajam\" - road strike - had stopped any chance of catching a bus from kathmandu to langtang for at least 2 days.</p>\r\nas my mates cracked their beers and resigned themselves to more waiting, i had the realization that i could not endure that smoggy hellhole another minute.  i decided i would walk to langtang - the way trekkers used to 30 years ago - right down that same road that any other day in this era would be chaotically choked with buses, cars and other implements of pedestrian death.\r\n<p id=\"yui_3_11_0_3_1386450473510_1564\">walking that road, leaving the city behind, stopping for noodles, meeting people, the villagers were drying their crops on tarpaulins laid out on the asphalt.  and quiet as a church. i managed to walk in one day what can be driven in 2 hours. there was one hotel in ranipauwa, where i stayed with some nice kids, and when i awoke the following morning and stepped out to look around, there it was.</p>\r\nCanon EF-S 15 -85 mm @ 35mm/f9.  Canon EOS Rebel T1i 1/160th second exposure @ ISO 200.  Camera Raw processed &amp; profiled with Adobe Photoshop CS5/Canon IPF 16 bit print plug-in for Photoshop.','ganesh & and helambu dawn','','publish','open','closed','','ganesh-helambu-dawn','','','2013-12-07 21:16:50','2013-12-07 21:16:50','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=330',20,'product','',0),(331,2,'2013-11-24 19:18:06','2013-11-24 19:18:06','','ganesh_and_helambu_dawn','','inherit','open','open','','ganesh_and_helambu_dawn','','','2013-11-24 19:18:06','2013-11-24 19:18:06','',330,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/ganesh_and_helambu_dawn.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(332,2,'2013-11-24 19:20:31','2013-11-24 19:20:31','<strong>from the lamjung himalaya, nepal</strong>','kharka & clouds','','publish','open','closed','','kharka-clouds','','','2013-11-24 19:20:31','2013-11-24 19:20:31','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=332',46,'product','',0),(333,2,'2013-11-24 19:20:00','2013-11-24 19:20:00','','kharka_and_clouds','','inherit','open','open','','kharka_and_clouds','','','2013-11-24 19:20:00','2013-11-24 19:20:00','',332,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/kharka_and_clouds.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(334,2,'2013-11-24 19:26:47','2013-11-24 19:26:47','<strong>From Japanese Camp</strong>\r\n\r\nwe spent a few days shuffling around on rocks stacked like dinner plates in order to visit makalu advanced camp - which lies 1000m above makalu basecamp and serves as the actual base for expeditions attempting to summit by the standard route.  it is tucked away up a tributary glacier of the barun at an altitiude of about 5700m, and every year an international city of tents grows here during expedition season.  i wanted to pay a visit to check out the scene &amp; speak some english.\r\n\r\nwe brought a snowstorm up with us, so everyone was hiding in their tent, but the sherpas invited us into one of the cook tents, and we swapped a few stories, drank some tea, and saw some state of the art high altitude cookware.  then i knocked on a few tent flaps &amp; met some pretty cool climbers.  that afternoon we returned in the elements to our tents here @ japanesese camp, an intermeditate stopping point along the glacier about 2/3 of the way up.\r\n\r\nthe evening broke up the storm and i was able to wander out into the vast expanse of rocks, freshly painted with the new fallen snow.  i loved the way the new snow filled in shadows beneath makalu, watching over us, fighting off the last clouds stubbornly clinging to her in the light of the setting sun.\r\n\r\nmerge of 4 photographs – Canon EF 24 -105 mm @ 35mm/f22.  Canon EOS 6D 1/80th second exposure @ ISO 320.  Camera Raw processed &amp; profiled with Adobe DNG Converter/Photoshop CS5/Canon IPF 16 bit print plug-in for Photoshop.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_336\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"585\"]<a href=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/makalu_sunset_from_japanese_camp_SAMPLE.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-336 \" alt=\"makalu_sunset_from_japanese_camp_SAMPLE\" src=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/makalu_sunset_from_japanese_camp_SAMPLE.jpg\" width=\"585\" height=\"396\" /></a> detail[/caption]','sunset on makalu (8481m)','','publish','open','closed','','sunset-on-makalu-8481m','','','2013-12-05 15:14:48','2013-12-05 15:14:48','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=334',16,'product','',0),(335,2,'2013-11-24 19:24:21','2013-11-24 19:24:21','','makalu_sunset_from_japanese_camp','','inherit','open','open','','makalu_sunset_from_japanese_camp','','','2013-11-24 19:24:21','2013-11-24 19:24:21','',334,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/makalu_sunset_from_japanese_camp.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(336,2,'2013-11-24 19:26:22','2013-11-24 19:26:22','','makalu_sunset_from_japanese_camp_SAMPLE','','inherit','open','open','','makalu_sunset_from_japanese_camp_sample','','','2013-11-24 19:26:22','2013-11-24 19:26:22','',334,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/makalu_sunset_from_japanese_camp_SAMPLE.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(337,2,'2013-11-24 19:49:01','2013-11-24 19:49:01','<strong>From Gore Camp - Baltoro Glacier, Pakistan</strong>\r\n\r\ncapturing detail in the nooks and crannies of ice and rock is the essence of mountain photography.  i was deeply inspired by the way that ansel adams worked with the texture of granite cliffs, desert badlands, or adobe, and i wanted to pay homage to him with the striations in these penitentes, following their pattern of weathering, silent sentinels shifting with the ice &amp; standing witness to the perfection of the baltoro.  the play of wind and temperature and it\'s microcosmic reflection of the forces that created these mountains is something wonderful to think about.\r\n\r\nmasherbrum was labelled  k1 from the first english surveys - the k being for karakoram - turkic for \"black rock\".  the local name, masherbrum, translates from balti as \"trigger mountain\" - in reference to the tilt of the summit block.\r\n\r\nmerge of 10 photographs - Canon EF-S 15 -85 mm @ 32mm/f29.  Canon EOS Rebel T1i 1/60th second exposure @ ISO 200.  Camera Raw processed &amp; profiled with Adobe Photoshop CS5/Canon IPF 16 bit print plug-in for Photoshop.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_339\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"587\"]<a href=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/masherbrum_and_penitentes_sample.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-339 \" alt=\"masherbrum_and_penitentes_sample\" src=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/masherbrum_and_penitentes_sample.jpg\" width=\"587\" height=\"396\" /></a> detail[/caption]','masherbrum & penitentes','','publish','open','closed','','masherbrum-penitentes','','','2013-12-05 16:23:45','2013-12-05 16:23:45','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=337',17,'product','',0),(338,2,'2013-11-24 19:46:28','2013-11-24 19:46:28','','masherbrum_and_penitentes','','inherit','open','open','','masherbrum_and_penitentes','','','2013-11-24 19:46:28','2013-11-24 19:46:28','',337,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/masherbrum_and_penitentes.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(339,2,'2013-11-24 19:48:30','2013-11-24 19:48:30','','masherbrum_and_penitentes_sample','','inherit','open','open','','masherbrum_and_penitentes_sample','','','2013-11-24 19:48:30','2013-11-24 19:48:30','',337,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/masherbrum_and_penitentes_sample.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(341,2,'2013-11-24 19:58:12','2013-11-24 19:58:12','<strong>from paiyu camp - karakoram range, pakistan</strong>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_343\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"353\"]<a href=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/shigar_riverbed_and_towers_SAMPLE.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-343\" alt=\"shigar_riverbed_and_towers_SAMPLE\" src=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/shigar_riverbed_and_towers_SAMPLE.jpg\" width=\"353\" height=\"238\" /></a> detail[/caption]','shigar river bed & trango towers','','trash','open','closed','','shigar-river-bed-trango-towers','','','2013-11-24 20:03:36','2013-11-24 20:03:36','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=341',0,'product','',0),(342,2,'2013-11-24 19:56:17','2013-11-24 19:56:17','','shigar_riverbed_and_towers','','inherit','open','open','','shigar_riverbed_and_towers','','','2013-11-24 19:56:17','2013-11-24 19:56:17','',341,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/shigar_riverbed_and_towers.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(343,2,'2013-11-24 19:57:46','2013-11-24 19:57:46','','shigar_riverbed_and_towers_SAMPLE','','inherit','open','open','','shigar_riverbed_and_towers_sample','','','2013-11-24 19:57:46','2013-11-24 19:57:46','',341,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/shigar_riverbed_and_towers_SAMPLE.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(344,2,'2013-11-24 20:01:01','2013-11-24 20:01:01','<strong>From Concordia - Karakoram Range, Pakistan</strong>\r\n\r\ni\'d had a rough day of it with my attempt to reach k2 basecamp derailed by explosive dysentery.  before crawling back into the tent i willed myself to wash my fouled gear and lay it out in the sun - then i passed out.\r\n\r\nwoke up in the evening &amp; indeed the weather signs were improving - and at last here was my first exposure to \"the shining wall\" - sunset on the absolutely one of a kind west face of gasherbrum IV.\r\n\r\ngasherbrum translates from balti as \"beautiful mountain\".  unbelievable as it is to fathom, this face has been climbed.  in 1985 wojciech kurtyka &amp; robert schauer climbed the complete face alpine style but had to abandon the summit in the face of exhaustion and bad weather.  still ranks in my book as one of the great achievements in the himalayas.\r\n\r\nCanon EF-S 15 -85 mm @ 85mm/f18.  Canon EOS Rebel T1i 1/125th second exposure @ ISO 200.  Camera Raw processed &amp; profiled with Adobe Photoshop CS5/Canon IPF 16 bit print plug-in for Photoshop.','sunset on gahserbrum IV with clouds','','publish','open','closed','','sunset-on-gahserbrum-iv-with-clouds','','','2013-12-04 01:48:59','2013-12-04 01:48:59','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=344',15,'product','',0),(345,2,'2013-11-24 19:59:43','2013-11-24 19:59:43','','gasherbrum_IV_and_clouds','','inherit','open','open','','gasherbrum_iv_and_clouds','','','2013-11-24 19:59:43','2013-11-24 19:59:43','',344,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/gasherbrum_IV_and_clouds.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(347,2,'2013-11-24 20:05:29','2013-11-24 20:05:29','<strong>from paiyu camp - karakoram range, pakistan</strong>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_343\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"353\"]<a href=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/shigar_riverbed_and_towers_SAMPLE.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-343\" alt=\"shigar_riverbed_and_towers_SAMPLE\" src=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/shigar_riverbed_and_towers_SAMPLE.jpg\" width=\"353\" height=\"238\" /></a> detail[/caption]','shigar river bed & towers','','draft','open','closed','','shigar-river-bed-towers','','','2013-12-11 16:15:36','2013-12-11 16:15:36','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=347',48,'product','',0),(348,2,'2013-11-24 20:09:01','2013-11-24 20:09:01','<strong>Manaslu Himalaya, Nepal - <strong>Ganesh Himalaya on the horizon</strong></strong>\r\n\r\na real turning point for me and learned something this day about my stubbornness.<strong><strong>\r\n</strong></strong>\r\n\r\nwanted to see manaslu across the way from the village of sama.  we were trying to make a real day of it so purna and i set out early &amp; ramesh baked tibetan bread in sama village behind us and then climbed up to us for lunch at a small col, with the kutang massif to our east and and sama ri just above to the west.\r\n\r\nthe northeastern slope appeared gradual enough, and a traversing ascent led eventually, quite close to the top, across a steep field of snow.  by now the route had crossed over so that the precipitous northwest face of sama dropped thousands of feet to the valley below, about 10 feet to the right.\r\n\r\npurna did not want to see me take the risk of crossing, and injury to me could ruin his professional reputation as well as put him &amp; ramesh needlessly at risk.  but i had summit fever &amp; this was terrain of a degree i\'d negotiated countless times when unguided.\r\n\r\nso i told them, wait for me there, and  i went anyway.  and i crossed some exposed terrain after that and topped out.  and i could see the ganesh himalaya, far on the horizon, glowing in perfection in the late afternoon sun, finally unobstructed at the very top.\r\n\r\nthe boys came up, and weren\'t annoyed, and we enjoyed this magic.  then we found a safer route back down and i\'d had my first really life changing day of the trip.\r\n\r\nmerge of 3 photographs – Canon EF-S 15 -85 mm @ 15mm/f11.  Canon EOS Rebel T1i 1/250th second exposure @ ISO 200.  Camera Raw processed &amp; profiled with Adobe Photoshop CS5/Canon IPF 16 bit print plug-in for Photoshop.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','the view from sama hill','','publish','open','closed','','the-view-from-sama-hill','','','2013-12-04 01:25:36','2013-12-04 01:25:36','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=348',14,'product','',0),(349,2,'2013-11-24 20:08:04','2013-11-24 20:08:04','','the_view_from_sama_hill','','inherit','open','open','','the_view_from_sama_hill','','','2013-11-24 20:08:04','2013-11-24 20:08:04','',348,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/the_view_from_sama_hill.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(350,2,'2013-11-24 20:17:58','2013-11-24 20:17:58','<strong>Lamjung Himalaya, Nepal</strong>\r\n\r\none of the great finds of my himalayan adventures - a private oasis to photograph the manaslu himalaya &amp; surroundings from an island in the clouds, scattered with wind whipped trees and primitive kharkas.\r\n\r\nsundar lies on the western shelf of the marsyangdi khola, a giant river which deeply cuts the range and divides the lamjung &amp; manaslu himalaya.  kharka means \"shelter\" and the area is used for pasture in the rainy months when the animals go up high.  dry as a bone in december 2009 when i took this.\r\n\r\nnice one to purna and ramesh for keeping the flame alive &amp; working with me to find this place.  hope to always be finding more.\r\n\r\nmerge of 15 photographs - Canon EF-S 15 -85 mm @ 15mm/f18.  Canon EOS Rebel T1i 1/40th second exposure @ ISO 200.  Camera Raw processed &amp; profiled with Adobe Photoshop CS5/Canon IPF 16 bit print plug-in for Photoshop.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_352\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"591\"]<a href=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/sundar_kharka_sample.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-352 \" alt=\"sundar_kharka_sample\" src=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/sundar_kharka_sample.jpg\" width=\"591\" height=\"396\" /></a> detail[/caption]','sundar kharka','','publish','open','closed','','sundar-kharka','','','2013-12-02 21:46:54','2013-12-02 21:46:54','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=350',13,'product','',0),(351,2,'2013-11-24 20:15:48','2013-11-24 20:15:48','','sundar_kharka','','inherit','open','open','','sundar_kharka','','','2013-11-24 20:15:48','2013-11-24 20:15:48','',350,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/sundar_kharka.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(352,2,'2013-11-24 20:17:34','2013-11-24 20:17:34','','sundar_kharka_sample','','inherit','open','open','','sundar_kharka_sample','','','2013-11-24 20:17:34','2013-11-24 20:17:34','',350,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/sundar_kharka_sample.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(353,2,'2013-11-24 20:26:17','2013-11-24 20:26:17','<strong>From the climb of Sama Hill - Around Manaslu Trek, Nepal</strong>\r\n\r\nhard to find a more wonderful and enchanting creature than a yak - the embodiment of the gentle buddhist giant.  we encountered them in scores on our climb of sama hill, which derives it\'s name from the village it looks down upon from across the budhi gandaki.\r\n\r\nyaks are treated poorly in nepal and thusly they are often skittish and afraid of humans pointing things at them.  hopefully this gentle giant was unexposed to such depradation and thus found himself willing to pose with the 8th tallest mountain on earth.\r\n\r\nCanon EF-S 15 -85 mm @ 19mm/f16.  Canon EOS Rebel T1i 1/50th second exposure @ ISO 200.  Camera Raw processed &amp; profiled with Adobe Photoshop CS5/Canon IPF 16 bit print plug-in for Photoshop.','yak & manaslu (8163m)','','publish','open','closed','','yak-manaslu-8163m','','','2013-12-02 21:21:09','2013-12-02 21:21:09','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=353',12,'product','',0),(354,2,'2013-11-24 20:22:28','2013-11-24 20:22:28','','yak_and_manaslu','','inherit','open','open','','yak_and_manaslu','','','2013-11-24 20:22:28','2013-11-24 20:22:28','',353,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/yak_and_manaslu.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(355,2,'2013-11-24 20:27:54','2013-11-24 20:27:54','<strong>Karakoram Range, Pakistan</strong>\r\n\r\na recurring phenomenon i experience with himalayan photography is that the very special shots arrive in bunches, usually around some fleeting magical moment in the mountains. the sunrise of august 15 was one of those moments. in 20 seconds i recorded 3 photographs of the sun kissing nameless tower and uli biaho as the swirling mist prepared to close in again. and just like that, it was gone. i have to admit, it was great to come back down to camp with everyone just waking up to cloudy skies. the effect was like a champagne cork - finally i could relax, i\'d gotten something i\'d come for.\r\n\r\nCanon EF-S 15 -85 mm @ 85mm/f11.  Canon EOS Rebel T1i 1/125th second exposure @ ISO 200.  Camera Raw processed &amp; profiled with Adobe Photoshop CS5/Canon IPF 16 bit print plug-in for Photoshop.','uli biaho (6109m)','','publish','open','closed','','uli-biaho-6109m','','','2013-12-02 14:34:39','2013-12-02 14:34:39','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=355',8,'product','',0),(356,2,'2013-11-24 20:27:07','2013-11-24 20:27:07','','uli_biaho','','inherit','open','open','','uli_biaho','','','2013-11-24 20:27:07','2013-11-24 20:27:07','',355,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/uli_biaho.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(357,2,'2013-11-24 20:32:08','2013-11-24 20:32:08','<strong>from urdukas camp - karakoram range, pakistan</strong>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_359\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"346\"]<a href=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/sunset_from_urdukas_SAMPLE.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-359\" alt=\"sunset_from_urdukas_SAMPLE\" src=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/sunset_from_urdukas_SAMPLE.jpg\" width=\"346\" height=\"238\" /></a> detail[/caption]','sunset on the baltoro','','trash','open','closed','','sunset-on-the-baltoro','','','2013-11-24 20:37:28','2013-11-24 20:37:28','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=357',0,'product','',0),(358,2,'2013-11-24 20:30:17','2013-11-24 20:30:17','','sunset_from_urdukas','','inherit','open','open','','sunset_from_urdukas','','','2013-11-24 20:30:17','2013-11-24 20:30:17','',357,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/sunset_from_urdukas.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(359,2,'2013-11-24 20:31:44','2013-11-24 20:31:44','','sunset_from_urdukas_SAMPLE','','inherit','open','open','','sunset_from_urdukas_sample','','','2013-11-24 20:31:44','2013-11-24 20:31:44','',357,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/sunset_from_urdukas_SAMPLE.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(360,2,'2013-11-24 20:35:08','2013-11-24 20:35:08','<strong>From the Baltoro Glacier - Karakoram Range, Pakistan</strong>\r\n\r\nstopped here on our way back down the baltoro in perfect weather - all the time in the world to contemplate the lovely trango towers reflected in a small pool in the texture of the glacier.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','trango reflections from urdukas','','publish','open','closed','','trango-reflections-from-urdukas','','','2013-12-15 14:51:24','2013-12-15 14:51:24','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=360',26,'product','',0),(361,2,'2013-11-24 20:34:10','2013-11-24 20:34:10','','trango_refections_from_urdukas','','inherit','open','open','','trango_refections_from_urdukas','','','2013-11-24 20:34:10','2013-11-24 20:34:10','',360,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/trango_refections_from_urdukas.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(363,2,'2013-11-24 20:38:58','2013-11-24 20:38:58','<strong>from urdukas camp - karakoram range, pakistan</strong>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_359\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"346\"]<a href=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/sunset_from_urdukas_SAMPLE.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-359\" alt=\"sunset_from_urdukas_SAMPLE\" src=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/sunset_from_urdukas_SAMPLE.jpg\" width=\"346\" height=\"238\" /></a> detail[/caption]','Sunset on the Baltoro','','publish','open','closed','','sunset-on-the-baltoro-2','','','2013-11-24 20:38:58','2013-11-24 20:38:58','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=363',45,'product','',0),(364,2,'2013-11-24 20:44:51','2013-11-24 20:44:51','<strong>from the baltoro glacier - karakoram range, pakistan</strong>','sun setting behind uli biaho (6109m)','','trash','open','closed','','sun-setting-behind-uli-biaho-6109m','','','2013-11-24 20:45:51','2013-11-24 20:45:51','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=364',0,'product','',0),(365,2,'2013-11-24 20:43:06','2013-11-24 20:43:06','','sunset_behind_uli_biaho','','inherit','open','open','','sunset_behind_uli_biaho','','','2013-11-24 20:43:06','2013-11-24 20:43:06','',364,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/sunset_behind_uli_biaho.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(366,2,'2013-11-24 20:50:06','2013-11-24 20:50:06','<strong>Annapurna Himalaya, Nepal</strong>\r\n\r\nanother obsessive quest for a fresh vista led me to namchung ri, an obscure hill in the central annapurna foothills.  the approach starts from pokhara via via taxi or the dreaded bus so i usually opt for the former.  then 1/2 a day hike up my secret valley &amp; through the maze up the flanks of namchung, whose top reveals the iconic machhapuchare, translated as \"fishtail\" in nepali bhasa.\r\n\r\ni made 2 attempts at the top and made it both times - the first time in a howling storm that obscured everything and soaked me through - this after a night huddling in a cave during a lightning storm, trying to master the intricacies of kindling bamboo &amp; wet wood.  epic failure in terms of getting a fire lit or getting my shot, but successful in that at least i knew how to get here again, and how to negotiate the labrynth of buffalo trails running up and down the hillside.\r\n\r\n1 month later i was back, and carrying a tent to boot - a rarity for me in the hospitable himalaya.  managed to shake out early and grab this one in a rare moment of good weather during the early monsoon.\r\n\r\nmerge of 13 photographs - Canon EF 24 -105 mm @ 105mm/f13.  Canon EOS 6D 1/200th second exposure @ ISO 400.  Camera Raw processed &amp; profiled with Adobe DNG Converter/Photoshop CS5/Canon IPF 16 bit print plug-in for Photoshop.\r\n<div></div>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_368\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"577\"]<a href=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/machhapuchare_and_surrounding_peaks_from_namchung_ri_SAMPLE.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-368 \" alt=\"machhapuchare_and_surrounding_peaks_from_namchung_ri_SAMPLE\" src=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/machhapuchare_and_surrounding_peaks_from_namchung_ri_SAMPLE.jpg\" width=\"577\" height=\"396\" /></a> detail[/caption]','macchapuchare (6997m) from namchung ri','','publish','open','closed','','macchapuchare-6997m-from-namchung-ri','','','2013-12-04 01:03:12','2013-12-04 01:03:12','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=366',6,'product','',0),(367,2,'2013-11-24 20:47:48','2013-11-24 20:47:48','','machhapuchare_and_surrounding_peaks_from_namchung_ri','','inherit','open','open','','machhapuchare_and_surrounding_peaks_from_namchung_ri','','','2013-11-24 20:47:48','2013-11-24 20:47:48','',366,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/machhapuchare_and_surrounding_peaks_from_namchung_ri.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(368,2,'2013-11-24 20:49:39','2013-11-24 20:49:39','','machhapuchare_and_surrounding_peaks_from_namchung_ri_SAMPLE','','inherit','open','open','','machhapuchare_and_surrounding_peaks_from_namchung_ri_sample','','','2013-11-24 20:49:39','2013-11-24 20:49:39','',366,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/machhapuchare_and_surrounding_peaks_from_namchung_ri_SAMPLE.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(369,2,'2013-11-24 20:54:22','2013-11-24 20:54:22','<strong>From the Baltoro Glacier - Karakoram Range, Pakistan</strong>\r\n\r\nwe spent considerable time in urdukas - and a couple of extra days no one could have planned for. on the day following this one we were jolted from our holiday quite violently when a boulder the size of a truck fell off the mountain and crashed through camp, killing 3 men and wounding 4 others.\r\n\r\ni will never forget the courage our team displayed in helping everyone they could. it also touched me to witness that the basic human need to give and receive kindness and compassion outstrips any nationality or class or party or whatever type of social division we impose upon ourselves. it was crystal clear to me in that moment. i hope i don\'t forget that as well.\r\n\r\nmerge of 4 photographs - Canon EF-S 15 -85 mm @ 85mm/f9.  Canon EOS Rebel T1i 1/100th second exposure @ ISO 200.  Camera Raw processed &amp; profiled with Adobe Photoshop CS5/Canon IPF 16 bit print plug-in for Photoshop.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','sun setting behind uli biaho (6109m)','','publish','open','closed','','sun-setting-behind-uli-biaho-6109m-2','','','2013-12-02 22:19:11','2013-12-02 22:19:11','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=369',32,'product','',0),(370,2,'2013-11-24 20:57:46','2013-11-24 20:57:46','<strong>From Urdukas Camp</strong>\r\n\r\nthese are the fabled great trango towers, with the sun setting and clouds swirling around them.  they are unique in shape, scope, awesomeness, and aesthetic to me in just about every way.  they are testpieces of alpinism, and while i will never stand on any of their extremely dangerous summits, i am glad to have seen such an ideal in my mountain journeys.  i am comforted that such places exist to feed a truth that i feel in my soul.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','trango sunset','','publish','open','closed','','trango-sunset','','','2013-12-14 18:49:41','2013-12-14 18:49:41','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=370',24,'product','',0),(371,2,'2013-11-24 20:57:08','2013-11-24 20:57:08','','trango_sunset','','inherit','open','open','','trango_sunset','','','2013-11-24 20:57:08','2013-11-24 20:57:08','',370,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/trango_sunset.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(372,2,'2013-11-24 21:00:06','2013-11-24 21:00:06','<strong>From Gore Camp - Baltoro Glacier, Pakistan</strong>\r\n\r\ni spent a lot of contemplation over whether i prefer morning or evening light on masherbrum &amp; her immense northeastern aspect.\r\n\r\nthe complexity of this awesome face is highlighted in different yet equally spectcular ways - depending upon the lighting conditions of morning or dusk.  she had been invisible in clouds on the way up, but as we retraced the baltoro in perfect weather, i had all the time in the world to absorb her awesomeness indeed - &amp; the contemplation - did i prefer her features in morning or evening light?\r\n\r\nmerge of 5 photographs - Canon EF-S 15 -85 mm @ 40mm/f16.  Canon EOS Rebel T1i 1/60th second exposure @ ISO 100.  Camera Raw processed &amp; profiled with Adobe Photoshop CS5/Canon IPF 16 bit print plug-in for Photoshop.','morning light on masherbrum (7821m)','','publish','open','closed','','morning-light-on-masherbrum-7821m','','','2013-12-03 14:19:37','2013-12-03 14:19:37','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=372',0,'product','',0),(373,2,'2013-11-24 20:59:13','2013-11-24 20:59:13','','morning_light_on_masherbrum','','inherit','open','open','','morning_light_on_masherbrum','','','2013-11-24 20:59:13','2013-11-24 20:59:13','',372,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/morning_light_on_masherbrum.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(374,2,'2013-11-24 21:02:13','2013-11-24 21:02:13','<strong>Karakoram range, Pakistan</strong>\r\n\r\nCanon EF-S 15 -85 mm @ 85mm/f11.  Canon EOS Rebel T1i 1/125th second exposure @ ISO 200.  Camera Raw processed &amp; profiled with Adobe Photoshop CS5/Canon IPF 16 bit print plug-in for Photoshop.','nameless tower (6239m)','','publish','open','closed','','nameless-tower-6239m','','','2013-12-05 13:14:57','2013-12-05 13:14:57','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=374',1,'product','',0),(375,2,'2013-11-24 21:01:29','2013-11-24 21:01:29','','nameless_tower','','inherit','open','open','','nameless_tower','','','2013-11-24 21:01:29','2013-11-24 21:01:29','',374,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/nameless_tower.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(376,2,'2013-11-24 21:06:17','2013-11-24 21:06:17','<strong>Night falling on the Manaslu Himalaya</strong>\r\n\r\nafter trekking around manaslu i wanted to take the trek to the next level by finding a new vantage point from which to photograph her &amp; her neighbors - so purna, ramesh &amp; i hunted around and tried to get up the hill above syange village in order to photograph the massif from across the marsyangdi valley.\r\n\r\nit took some doing - hacking through jungle &amp; a few detours - but we found the right ridge and most importantly we found water above the trees.  thusly we were able to make a go of a day of going as high as we could up into the foothills of the lamjung himalaya during our 7 day mini-expedition.\r\n\r\nthe climb of sundar ri culminated in this sunset on our descent.  the southwest faces of phungi himal, manaslu, ngadi chuli, himal chuli, and boudha himal float above the clouds arriving from india, crashing into the range, and funneling up the marsyangdi.  from here you can see 3 of the 48 tallest mountains on earth.\r\n\r\nmerge of 11 photographs - Canon EF-S 15 -85 mm @ 15mm/f10.  Canon EOS Rebel T1i 1/80th second exposure @ ISO 100.  Camera Raw processed &amp; profiled with Adobe Photoshop CS5/Canon IPF 16 bit print plug-in for Photoshop.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_377\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"522\"]<a href=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/sunset_from_sundar_sample1.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-377 \" alt=\"sunset_from_sundar_sample\" src=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/sunset_from_sundar_sample1.jpg\" width=\"522\" height=\"396\" /></a> detail[/caption]','sunset from sundar','','publish','open','closed','','sunset-from-sundar-2','','','2013-12-02 17:38:57','2013-12-02 17:38:57','',0,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=376',2,'product','',0),(377,2,'2013-11-24 21:03:48','2013-11-24 21:03:48','','sunset_from_sundar_sample','','inherit','open','open','','sunset_from_sundar_sample-2','','','2013-11-24 21:03:48','2013-11-24 21:03:48','',376,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/sunset_from_sundar_sample1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(378,2,'2013-11-24 21:05:26','2013-11-24 21:05:26','','sunset_from_sundar','','inherit','open','open','','sunset_from_sundar-2','','','2013-11-24 21:05:26','2013-11-24 21:05:26','',376,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/sunset_from_sundar1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(380,2,'2013-12-03 14:07:05','2013-12-03 14:07:05','<strong>From Gore Camp - Baltoro Glacier, Pakistan</strong>\n\ni spent a lot of contemplation over whether i prefer morning or evening light on masherbrum &amp; her immense northeastern aspect.\n\nthe complexity of this awesome face is highlighted in different yet equally spectcular ways - depending upon the lighting conditions of morning or dusk.  she had been invisible in clouds on the way up, but as we retraced the baltoro in perfect weather, i had all the time in the world to absorb her awesomeness indeed - &amp; the contemplation - did i prefer her features in morning or evening light?\n\nmerge of 5 photographs - Canon EF-S 15 -85 mm @ 40mm/f16.  Canon EOS Rebel T1i 1/60th second exposure @ ISO 100.  Camera Raw processed &amp; profiled with Adobe Photoshop CS5/Canon IPF 16 bit print plug-in for Photoshop.','morning light on masherbrum (7821m)','','inherit','open','open','','372-autosave-v1','','','2013-12-03 14:07:05','2013-12-03 14:07:05','',372,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/372-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(381,2,'2013-11-27 04:35:02','2013-11-27 04:35:02','[justified_image_grid preset=3 row_height=300 height_deviation=40 caption=fade min_height=600 orderby=menu_order last_row=flexible disable_cropping=yes developer_link=hide load_more=scroll load_more_limit=6 recent_posts=yes recents_post_type=product]','<span class=\"small\">Doug Kofsky</span><br /><strong>M O U N T A I N S C A P E S</strong','','inherit','open','open','','38-revision-v1','','','2013-11-27 04:35:02','2013-11-27 04:35:02','',38,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/38-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(382,2,'2013-11-27 04:35:54','2013-11-27 04:35:54','[justified_image_grid preset=3 row_height=300 height_deviation=40 caption=fade min_height=600 orderby=menu_order last_row=flexible disable_cropping=yes developer_link=hide load_more=scroll load_more_limit=6 recent_posts=yes recents_post_type=product]','<span class=\"small\">D o u g  K o f s k y</span><br /><strong>M O U N T A I N S C A P E S</strong','','inherit','open','open','','38-revision-v1','','','2013-11-27 04:35:54','2013-11-27 04:35:54','',38,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/38-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(383,2,'2013-11-27 04:47:30','2013-11-27 04:47:30','[justified_image_grid preset=3 row_height=300 height_deviation=40 caption=fade min_height=600 orderby=menu_order last_row=flexible disable_cropping=yes developer_link=hide load_more=scroll load_more_limit=6 recent_posts=yes recents_post_type=product]','<strong>M O U N T A I N S C A P E S</strong>','','inherit','open','open','','38-revision-v1','','','2013-11-27 04:47:30','2013-11-27 04:47:30','',38,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/38-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(384,1,'2013-11-27 21:12:12','2013-11-27 21:12:12','','doug_kofsky_background','','inherit','open','open','','doug_kofsky_background','','','2013-11-27 21:12:12','2013-11-27 21:12:12','',86,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/doug_kofsky_background.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(385,1,'2013-11-27 21:12:22','2013-11-27 21:12:22','<p dir=\"ltr\">Coming to the himalaya was like meeting friends i had heard much about.  Reading of the  struggles in the valleys and on the flanks, in the irrational pursuit to reach  the tops of these great mountains - these stories had inspired such vivid images in my mind, that it followed that i would take the pilgrimage here as a matter of course.</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">My first journey was around Dhaulagiri in 2008, the seventh tallest mountain in the world.  As suddenly as we approached, newly opened eyes to this foreign landscape, as a photographer, I knew exactly what</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">needed to be done.  I had suddenly seemed to synergize my two great loves- photography &amp; mountains.  That first trip has been followed by 4 more, each journey its own artistic &amp; technical evolution from the last.</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">My dream is to photograph the great himalayan peaks - the impossible geography of ultimate m</p>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-112\" alt=\"doug_and_friends\" src=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/doug_and_friends-300x200.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" />\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">ountain form.  There are 14 mountains on earth whose tops reach more than 8000 meters above sea level.   with my eyes &amp; camera i have seen &amp; photographed 10 of them.  Around these “sacred” summits lie countless other examples of mountain architecture, in distillations approaching perfection - what i am looking for - the most beautiful mountains in the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<div></div>\r\n<a title=\"The Gallery\" href=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/gallery/\">View the Gallery</a>','<span class=\"small\">About</span><br />Doug Kofsky','','inherit','open','open','','86-revision-v1','','','2013-11-27 21:12:22','2013-11-27 21:12:22','',86,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/86-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(386,1,'2013-11-27 21:13:52','2013-11-27 21:13:52','<a href=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/the-location/doug_and_valley/#main\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-118\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-118\" alt=\"doug_and_valley\" src=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/doug_and_valley.jpg\" width=\"537\" height=\"357\" /></a>hard to know where to start to quantify my experience of the cross cultural adventures undertaken to put myself in position - none of it could have been done without the excellent professional services of local guides in the respective countries of nepal and pakistan.\r\n\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">within their national borders these 2 countries hold 13 of the 14 tallest peaks on earth.  because of logistical considerations i have now visited nepal on 4 occasions &amp; pakistan once.</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">nepal is the hub of the himalayan tourism destination wheel, a hindu/somewhat buddhist amalgam of contradiction that starts to obtain its own logic only upon closer inspection than the patient can at times be expected to contrive.  everything starts and ends in the city of kathmandu - which once navigated is the final barrier to nirvana.</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">many national parks are demarcated within nepal for trekking tourism, and there are among the locals some of the most hospitable hosts and indomitable guides in the world.  truly at present a mecca for anyone who wants to see giant mountains and accompanying culture.  tourist inflation is soaring, as globalisation adjusts prices to near western levels in tourist hotspots, in the 3rd poorest country in the world.</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">But what you see here cannot help but change you.  Just everything is different.  And in a beautiful way, Nepal is so open to adventure - the feeling that with a pile of rupees in your hand &amp; a good pair of boots, you can go just about anywhere.  cheers to that.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Pakistan was a different case - the level of apprehension even at the name for americans now is steadily escalating, and the perception of that country has never been lower.  I am very lucky - I was able to visit in a period of stability during the summer of 2011 - i had put it off &amp; put it off, only to be able to take the plunge after a rought episode at work prompted a personal spell of recklessness - when i bought a plane ticket.</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">best decision of my life - i loved every minute of pakistan, even when i was bitching:)  people there were so cool - present, not scamming you, open to real discussion, sad over the loss of friendship between our countries.  i met some wonderful guys &amp; pray we can turn it around.</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In northern pakistan the himalayas end on the flanks of a mountain named nanga parbat.  another mountain range lies to the north of here, the karakoram range - with dimensions attaining similar magnitude in scale.  I was blessed to trek the baltoro glacier at least once, and photograph “the throne room of the mountain gods.”  The scale and architecture of these peaks is on another level - and the weather pattern in the karakoram is very different than the himalaya - with larger glaciers &amp; more instability.  for 15 days we drank water stained brown with the silty dust that rains off this similarly colored landscape.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">himalaya - \"abode of snow\" (sanskrit)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">karakoram - \"black rock\" (turkic)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">himal - \"mountain\" (sanskrit)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">chuli - \"mountain\" (nepali)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">tse - \"mountain\" (tibetan)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">la - \"high pass\" (tibetan)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">ri - \"hill\" (tibetan)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">khola - \"river\" (nepali)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">sundar - \"handsome\" (nepali)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">kharka - \"shelter\" (nepali)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">machha - \"fish\" (nepali)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">puchare - \"tail\" (nepali)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">brum - \"mountain\" (balti)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">gasher - \"beautiful\" (balti)</p>\r\n<b id=\"docs-internal-guid-612e253c-82c9-e896-89ff-aeca99288257\">masher - \"trigger\" (balti)</b>\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<h2>A Section Title</h2>\r\n&nbsp;','The Location','','inherit','open','open','','88-revision-v1','','','2013-11-27 21:13:52','2013-11-27 21:13:52','',88,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/88-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(387,1,'2013-11-27 21:14:16','2013-11-27 21:14:16','<p dir=\"ltr\">With the digital era photography has risen like a phoenix from it’s own ashes.  there is a level of control for the photographer (and especially the home photographer) previously unknown in the art.  From photoshop, photomerging, rgb printers, high sensitivity sensors, lens stabilization -</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">When my photography heroes came to the himalaya before me, they shot on film, and the earliest shot with tripods -</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">vittorio sella came up the baltoro in 1909 with the duke of abruzzi and really introduced these mountains to the world - some of his photography here</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"http://www.panopticongallery.com/artist/vittorio_sella/#Vittorio_Sella_29.jpg\">http://www.panopticongallery.com/artist/vittorio_sella/#Vittorio_Sella_29.jpg</a></p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">for american nature photographers ansel adams is the photographer to which all others seem a footnote - &amp; to his credit, his technique is very democratic, the zone system outlined in his masterpiece book “the negative” being the foundation upon which my photography is based.  as a man of his time, he shot with a large format camera &amp; a tripod, and of course the results speak for themselves</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ansel_Adams\">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ansel_Adams</a></p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">a photographer seminal to photographing just the himalayas is shiro shirahata.  his 2 folio books “nepal himalaya” &amp; “karakoram” begin to see the mountains themselves as characters - his books are portrait albums of the tallest mountains on earth.  his style represents the height of expedition style - on his treks he brought armies of porters, they hunted game, carried a large format camera &amp; a tripod.</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"http://www.shiro-shirahata.net/garalley.html\">http://www.shiro-shirahata.net/garalley.html</a></p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">galen rowell i see as an evolution to “alpine style”.  his tool of choice was the nikkor 20 mm f4 on a 35mm dslr - in other words, he could handhold the smaller, lighter, wide lensed camera, and get himself just about anywhere - a great climber in his own right with that camera.</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"http://www.mountainlight.com/gallery.html\">http://www.mountainlight.com/gallery.html</a></p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">just as the early siege expeditions to climb the great peaks have evolved to more lightweight attempts, we can see here that mountain photography has now paralleled that evolution through “alpine style” to what is now called “ultralight”.</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">lens stabilization and the high sensitivities obtainable by digital sensors have made it possible now to shoot without a tripod - a seriously clunky encumbrance on uneven terrain in the mountains.  a cart full of giant photo plates has evolved to a backpack full of xray sensitive film cartridges and is now solid state media cards that you can slip in your pocket.  And everything has to get safely back from asia.</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">shirahata - the culmination of expedition style</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">rowell - the dawn of alpine style and the nikkor 20 mm - evolution - but still carried film</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">photoshop.  rgb printers.</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">the process - photoshopping &amp; photomerging - taking multiple photographs - high sensitivity sensors &amp; handheld - lens stabilizationthe images are merged - the advantage being that you can them make them pretty big as the combined effect makes for a massive image able</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">photography “alpine style”</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">baryta paper - baryllium - testing - laboriously profiled</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">homemade - hand signed (image)</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">gear i have used that has made a difference</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">canon eos rebel t1i</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">canon efs 15 - 85 mm is usm</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">canon efs 18 - 200 mm</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">nikkor 50 mm f1.2</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">canon 6d</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">canon ef 24 -105 mm</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">canon ef 70 -200 mm t4</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">brunton 26w solar charger</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">schneider polarizer</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">photoshop cs4 &amp; cs5</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">ipf 6300 print plugin for photoshop</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">about sizing</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">i have unlimited editions of everything in their folio size -</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">for larger blah blah limited editions</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">if you can dream it - i might be able to print it!  feel free to inquire about custom sizing over and above the x - large size!  some of them go even bigger...</p>','The Process','','inherit','open','open','','125-revision-v1','','','2013-11-27 21:14:16','2013-11-27 21:14:16','',125,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/125-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(388,1,'2013-11-27 21:25:22','2013-11-27 21:25:22','[justified_image_grid preset=3 row_height=300 height_deviation=40 caption=fade min_height=600 orderby=menu_order custom_width=1200 last_row=flexible disable_cropping=yes developer_link=hide load_more=scroll load_more_limit=6 recent_posts=yes recents_post_type=product]','<strong>M O U N T A I N S C A P E S</strong>','','inherit','open','open','','38-revision-v1