 the area is used for pasture in the rainy months when the animals go up high.  dry as a bone in december 2009 when i took this.\n\nnice one to purna and ramesh for keeping the flame alive &amp; working with me to find this place.  hope to always be finding more.\n\nmerge of 15 photographs - Canon EF-S 15 -85 mm @ 15mm/f18.  Canon EOS Rebel T1i 1/40th second exposure @ ISO 200.  Camera Raw processed &amp; profiled with Adobe Photoshop CS5/Canon IPF 16 bit print plug-in for Photoshop.\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_352\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"591\"]<a href=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/sundar_kharka_sample.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-352 \" alt=\"sundar_kharka_sample\" src=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/content/uploads/2013/11/sundar_kharka_sample.jpg\" width=\"591\" height=\"396\" /></a> detail[/caption]','sundar kharka','','inherit','open','open','','350-autosave-v1','','','2013-12-02 21:46:40','2013-12-02 21:46:40','',350,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/350-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(427,2,'2013-12-02 22:07:46','2013-12-02 22:07:46','<p dir=\"ltr\">With the digital era photography has risen like a phoenix from it’s own ashes.  there is a level of control for the photographer (and especially the home photographer) previously unknown in the art.  From photoshop, photomerging, rgb printers, high sensitivity sensors, lens stabilization -</p>\r\n I am attempt to reinterpret many of the standards set forth by my photography heroes who came to the himalaya before me.  Of course they shot on film, and the earliest shot with tripods -\r\n\r\nVittorio Sella came up the baltoro in 1909 with the duke of abruzzi and really introduced these mountains to the world - and he shot on 30 x 40 cm glass plates!  The abbruzzi expedition photos are magnificent and have touched the heart of many a mountaineer.  some of his photography here:  <a title=\"vittorio sella\" href=\"http://www.panopticongallery.com/artist/vittorio_sella/#Vittorio_Sella_29.jpg\" target=\