h sensitivities obtainable by digital sensors have made it possible now to shoot without a tripod - a seriously clunky encumbrance on uneven terrain in the mountains.  a cart full of giant photo plates has evolved to a backpack full of xray sensitive film cartridges and is now solid state media cards that you can slip in your pocket.  And everything has to get safely back from asia.</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">shirahata - the culmination of expedition style</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">rowell - the dawn of alpine style and the nikkor 20 mm - evolution - but still carried film</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">photoshop.  rgb printers.</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">the process - photoshopping &amp; photomerging - taking multiple photographs - high sensitivity sensors &amp; handheld - lens stabilizationthe images are merged - the advantage being that you can them make them pretty big as the combined effect makes for a massive image able</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">photography “alpine style”</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">baryta paper - baryllium - testing - laboriously profiled</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">homemade - hand signed (image)</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">gear i have used that has made a difference</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">canon eos rebel t1i</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">canon efs 15 - 85 mm is usm</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">canon efs 18 - 200 mm</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">nikkor 50 mm f1.2</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">canon 6d</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">canon ef 24 -105 mm</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">canon ef 70 -200 mm t4</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">brunton 26w solar charger</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">schneider polarizer</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">photoshop cs4 &amp; cs5</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">ipf 6300 print plugin for photoshop</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">about sizing</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">i have unlimited editions of everything in their folio size -</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">for larger blah blah limited editions</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">if you can dream it - i might be able to print it!  feel free to inquire about custom sizing over and above the x - large size!  some of them go even bigger...</p>','The Process','','inherit','open','open','','125-revision-v1','','','2013-12-02 22:07:46','2013-12-02 22:07:46','',125,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/125-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(428,2,'2013-12-02 22:18:41','2013-12-02 22:18:41','<strong>From the Baltoro Glacier - Karakoram Range, Pakistan</strong>\n\nwe spent considerable time in urdukas - and a couple of extra days no one could have planned for. on the day following this one we were jolted from our holiday quite violently when a boulder the size of a truck fell off the mountain and crashed through camp, killing 3 men and wounding 4 others.\n\ni will never forget the courage our team displayed in helping everyone they could. it also touched me to witness that the basic human need to give and receive kindness and compassion outstrips any nationality or class or party or whatever type of social division we impose upon ourselves. it was crystal clear to me in that moment. i hope i don\'t forget that as well.\n\nstitch of 4 photographs canon efs 15-85 @ 85mm f9 eos rebel t1i 1/00sec 200iso raw photoshop cs5 mac\n\nmerge of 4 photographs - Canon EF-S 15 -85 mm @ 85mm/f9.  Canon EOS Rebel T1i 1/60th second exposure @ ISO 200.  Camera Raw processed &amp; profiled with Adobe Photoshop CS5/Canon IPF 16 bit print plug-in for Photoshop.\n\n&nbsp;','sun setting behind uli biaho (6109m)','','inherit','open','open','','369-autosave-v1','','','2013-12-02 22:18:41','2013-12-02 22:18:41','',369,'http://dev.dougkofsky.com/369-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(429,2,'2013-12-02 22:21:33','2013-12-02 22:21:33','[justified_image_grid preset=4 row_height=450 height_deviation=10 caption=fade min_height=600 orderby=menu_order last_row=flexible disable_cr