s, in the irrational pursuit to reach  the tops of these great mountains - these stories had inspired such vivid images in my mind, that it followed i would take the pilgrimage here as a matter of course.  My first journey was around Dhaulagiri in 2008, the seventh tallest mountain in the world.  As suddenly as we approached, newly opened eyes to this foreign landscape, as a photographer, I knew exactly what needed to be done.  I had suddenly seemed to synergize my two great loves- photography &amp; mountains.  That first trip has been followed by 4 more, each journey its own artistic &amp; technical evolution from the last.</p>\r\n<b><b> </b></b>My dream is to photograph the great himalayan peaks - the impossible geography of ultimate mountain form.  There are 14 mountains on earth whose tops reach more than 8000 meters above sea level.   with my eyes &amp; camera i have seen &amp; photographed 10 of them.  Around these “sacred” summits lie countless other examples of mountain architecture, in distillations approaching perfection - what i am looking for - the most beautiful mountains in the world.\r\n<div>a little more here</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>and a little more</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>and a little more</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>ya know?</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>doug kofsky</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>space</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>test</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><a title=\"The Gallery\" href=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/gallery/\">View the Gallery</a></div>','<span class=\"small\">About</span><br />Doug Kofsky','','inherit','open','open','','86-revision-v1','','','2013-12-18 17:52:03','2013-12-18 17:52:03','',86,'http://162.243.233.67/dougkofsky/86-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(567,2,'2013-12-18 18:25:31','2013-12-18 18:25:31','<p dir=\"ltr\">my dream is to document the great himalayan peaks of the world - to convey in photography the feeling of standing in their presence.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">my first expedition to asia was in 2008 