-12-20 02:47:49','<p dir=\"ltr\">my vision is to photograph the great himalayan peaks of the world and convey the feeling of standing in their presence.  in the largest sizes i can.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">the inspiration came some time back, when i lost a good friend and realized that the time had come to do those things i had always said i would do someday.  first on that list was traveling to to himalaya, in particular k2 in northern pakistan, the 2nd tallest mountain in the world.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">i was pretty concerned about visiting pakistan, so decided first to try my hand with altitude in somewhat mellower country of nepal.  this was in 2008 , when i made the trek around dhaulagiri I, seventh tallest.  i have since returned to nepal 3 more times to photograph the incredible mountains here and enjoy the incredible hospitality of the people.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">in 2011 i f felt seasoned enough and in a sort of life crossroads i bought a plane ticket to pakistan, to join an expedition to the baltoro glacier and the foot of k2.  this was a dream 10 years in the making, and my original mountain valhalla, for which i was willing to stick my neck out a little.  for k2 and it\'s surroundings are places that have inspired me like no other - not only for their singular architecture and impressively bold form, but for the inspiration taken from the stories written in human struggle to climb them, k2 in particular, the \"mountain of mountains\".  in books and photos they have captured my imagination for as long as i can remember.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">there is a spirituality to these places for me - and i think that as a photographer knowing what to shoot is as important as knowing how to shoot - the vision.  in the himalayas i am able to find this &amp; synergize 2 of my  passions - the most beautiful mountains in the world and photography.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">doug k</p>\r\n\r\n<div><a title=\"The Gallery\" href=\"http://dev.dougkofsky.com/gallery/\">View the Gallery</a></div>','<span class=\"small\">About</span><br />Doug Kofsky','','inherit','open','open','','86-revision-v1','','','2013-12-20 02:47:49','2013-12-20 02:47:49','',86,'http://162.243.233.67/dougkofsky/86-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(570,2,'2013-12-20 02:51:43','2013-12-20 02:51:43','<p dir=\"ltr\">my vision is to photograph the great himalayan peaks of the world and convey the feeling of standing in their presence.  in the largest sizes i can.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">the inspiration came some time back, when i lost a good friend and realized that the time had come to do those things i had always said i would do someday.  first on that list was traveling to to himalayas, in particular k2 in northern pakistan, the 2nd tallest mountain in the world.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">i was pretty concerned about visiting pakistan, so decided first to try my hand with altitude in the somewhat mellower country of nepal.  this was in 2008 , when i made the trek around dhaulagiri, seventh tallest.  i have since returned to nepal 3 more times to explore and photograph the incredible mountains here and enjoy the impeccable hospitality of the people.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">in 2011 i f felt seasoned enough to try pakistan - inspired by friends who had been and had wonderful things to say - so in a sort of life crossroads i bought a plane ticket to islamabad to join an expedition to the baltoro glacier and the foot of k2.  this was a dream 10 years in the making, and my original mountain valhalla, for which i was willing to stick my neck out a little.  for k2 and it\'s surroundings are places that have inspired me like no other - not only for their singular architecture and impressively bold form, but for the inspiration taken from the stories written in human struggle to climb them, k2 in particular, the \"mountain of mountains\".  in books and photos they have captured my imagination for as long as i can remember.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">there is a spirituality to these places for 